articles.title: N12 - "It is not possible to move on to tomorrow's news": the attack shocked... - mako
articles.description: This article reports on a shooting attack in the Israeli settlement of Alon, in which four Israelis were killed and four others injured. Eyewitnesses describe the attack and demand increased security measures in the settlement. The article also includes information on the initial investigation into the attack, which suggests that two armed attackers opened fire on a restaurant in the settlement before being neutralized by a civilian with a gun. The settlement's spokesperson calls for government action to restore a sense of security.

articles.title: "Wants to finish as a real football player, an important player" - One
articles.description: This article discusses the recent signing of Itay Shechter to Hapoel Petah Tikva and his reasons for choosing the team. Shechter explains that he chose the team because of their large and passionate fanbase, and also because of his close friend and teammate, Idan Vered, who influenced his decision. Shechter also discusses his love for the game and his desire to continue playing for at least another season.

articles.author: mako
articles.title: An end to the unbearable spam? The new update of WhatsApp - mako
articles.description: WhatsApp has introduced a new feature that will allow users to automatically block unwanted or unidentified calls. The new option will help "filter spam, fraud, and calls from unidentified people for increased protection," according to the company. Users can activate the feature by going to WhatsApp settings and selecting "calls" under privacy settings, then selecting "silence unknown callers." All notifications from those numbers will be silenced and will not appear on the screen, but the calls will still be listed in the call log. Additionally, WhatsApp has introduced a new privacy check feature that covers several important categories, including the ability to choose who can contact you.

articles.title: Hadas Klein at the hearing against Eli Tzipori: "My grandparents were in labor camps, will they tell me that I am a descendant of Eva Hitler?" - Walla! Barangay
articles.description: This article discusses the defamation lawsuit filed by the State Commission against Eli Zippori, who allegedly conducted a smear campaign against commission member Hadass Klein. The judge denied Zippori's request to dismiss the case, and during the hearing, Klein's lawyer argued that Zippori engaged in a clear campaign of harassment and defamation. Klein is seeking compensation of 5 million shekels for the alleged harm to her reputation and privacy.

articles.title: Champions League qualifiers: Maccabi Haifa will meet the Maroon Spartans from Malta - Haaretz
articles.description: This article reports that Maccabi Haifa will face Maltese team Hibernians in the first qualifying round of the Champions League. The first game will take place in Malta on July 11 or 12, with the return leg in Israel a week later. Hibernians is considered an easy draw for Maccabi Haifa, but the Maltese team has recently invested in its squad and won the Maltese league title last season. The article provides some background information on Hibernians' players and coach, as well as Maccabi Haifa's recent achievements in European competitions.
